🧭 Project Overview

In this project, we use Terraform to provision an AWS EC2 Key Pair using Infrastructure as Code (IaC). Instead of manually creating a key pair through the AWS Management Console, 
Terraform allows us to define the resource declaratively and deploy it consistently across environments.

This introduces one of the core DevOps principles: automating infrastructure provisioning.

🎯 Objective
Create an AWS EC2 Key Pair using Terraform
Store the public key in AWS
Understand the role of SSH key pairs in cloud environments
Learn how Terraform manages cloud resources declaratively

