🔐 Security Best Practices
Never commit private keys (id_rsa) to Git repositories.
Store private keys securely with appropriate file permissions (chmod 600).
Use descriptive key names for different environments (e.g., dev, staging, prod).
Rotate SSH keys periodically.
Prefer IAM roles or cloud-native identity mechanisms over SSH where possible.

